	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=99391"><span id="Scholar">malacar</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">51 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.66]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'm a lvl 21 bar shaman and I have found that the best stratagy tward getting the essence is to go to perma, fight some goblins for exp and blood and about every thrid time you have to med or zone out of perma due to one to many mendicants making you into Barbarian Barbeque, run up to the people camping the giants and ask them if they have any. (also ask for ivory while you're there cause the giants drop that too from time to time)<br/><br/>Let them know that its an inportant ingreediant that you can only get from the giants and ask if you can buy any from them.&nbsp;&nbsp;At that point also bank for them... buy their Fine Steel drops at a good price for them, and ask if they need ya to bring back any supplies or anything.  Be nice and friendly and it goes along way to getting essence, while possibly making a small profit from the banking jobs.  <br/><br/>Currently I have a very good working relationship with most of my sources for the essence.  Alot of them even save it for me now.  I bank for almost cost so they don't lose as much plat as they would banking with a lowbee out to prove that bandits do exist in everfrost.  In return I normally get essence free of charge or occasionally for a plat a piece.  Not bad concidering when I started asking half of them were destroying it cause they had no idea what it was for.<br/><br/>The important thing is to be nice and sociable and helpfull to the high lvl guys camping the giants, it really is.  Go the extra mile and you'll be rewarded.  At a vendor (if you get lucky enough to find it at a vendor) expect to pay about a plat for goblin blood, less than a gold per brandy and a little less than a plat for the essence if your charisma is good.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
